Comparison of soft clip base abundances

Soft clip data prep

Inner join of soft clip counts from all methods. Inner join will make sure no read ID is included if it was not aligned after adapter trimming by any method. This makes the comparison consistent across methods. To make for a better visualization later, all soft clip sums greater than 200 bases were discarded. These are negligible in data points as can be seen in the individual plots.

raw <- raw %>% 
    filter(SumSClips<200) %>%
    rename(RawSClips = SumSClips)
snikt <- snikt %>% 
    filter(SumSClips<200) %>%
    rename(SniktSClips = SumSClips)
guppy <- guppy %>% 
    filter(SumSClips<200) %>%
    rename(GuppySClips = SumSClips)
sClips <- inner_join(raw, snikt, by = "ReadID") %>%
    inner_join(guppy, by = "ReadID")
dim(sClips)
## [1] 348049      4
summary(sClips)
##     ReadID            RawSClips       SniktSClips       GuppySClips

Reformat columns to make a long table

sClips <- sClips %>% pivot_longer(cols = c(RawSClips, SniktSClips, GuppySClips), names_to = "Method", values_to = "SoftClips")

Plot soft clip distribution as histogram

sClipHist <- sClips %>% 
    ggplot(aes(SoftClips, fill = Method)) +
    geom_histogram(position = 'dodge', binwidth = 5) +
    scale_fill_discrete(name = "", breaks = c('RawSClips', 'GuppySClips', 'SniktSClips'),
                        labels = c("Raw reads", "Guppy trimmed reads", "SNIKT trimmed reads")) +
    labs(title = "Frequency of soft clipped bases per read before and after QC", x = "Number of soft clipped bases", y = "Frequency of reads") +
    theme_bw() +
    theme(legend.position = "bottom")
sClipHist

ggsave("soft_clip_comparison.png", sClipHist, width = 10, height = 5)
ggsave("soft_clip_comparison.pdf", sClipHist, width = 10, height = 5)

Plot soft clip distribution as density

sClips %>% 
    ggplot(aes(SoftClips, color = Method, group = Method)) +
    geom_density(position = 'identity', alpha = 0.6, adjust = 2) +
    scale_fill_discrete(breaks = c('RawSClips', 'GuppySClips', 'SniktSClips'))
